Posco to Reduce Stainless Steel Prices in May on Nickel Costs

-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 
2011-04-28T09:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/posco-to-reduce-stainless-steel-prices-in-may-on-nickel-costs.html
Posco (005490) , the worldâ€™s second-biggest
maker of stainless steel, will cut domestic prices of stainless
steel products by 100,000 won per metric ton after prices of
nickel, a key raw material, declined.  Prices of 300-series hot-rolled coil will fall by 2.5
percent to 3.9 million won ($3,638) in May, the Pohang, South
Korea-based company, said today in an e-mailed statement. Prices
of the 300-series cold-rolled products will drop by 2.3 percent
to 4.17 million won, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
